<title>BELGIUM: BELGIAN METALS, ENGINEERING SECTOR SEES IMPROVEMENT.</title>
<headline>BELGIAN METALS, ENGINEERING SECTOR SEES IMPROVEMENT.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-07-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Employers in Belgium's metals, plastics processing and engineering sector expect the economy to improve in the short term, sector organisation Fabrimetal said in a report on the first quarter published on Tuesday.</p>
<p>But, it said, in the electrical engineering, electronics and transport equipment sub-sectors a downward trend was expected in the coming months.</p>
<p>In the first quarter of 1997 deliveries and order books showed a favourable trend, while managers' employment, prices and production forecasts were altogether negative.</p>
<p>First quarter deliveries were up by nearly three percent compared with the first three months of 1996. Year on year, deliveries are up only two percent.</p>
<p>Deliveries fell in March due to a strike at Renault's Belgian car assembly plant over the plant's planned closure, Fabrimetal noted.</p>
